modules.description: Handles positioning and layout calculations for terminal images using the Kitty graphics protocol. Works with integer-based coordinates and dimensions to determine image placement within terminal cells. Useful for rendering images at specific screen positions while respecting terminal cell boundaries.

Handles image identifier creation and validation for terminal graphics operations. Works with integer values to produce validated image identifiers used in terminal rendering. Used to ensure safe image reference IDs when sending graphics commands to the terminal.

This module implements the Kitty terminal graphics protocol for displaying and manipulating images directly in terminal applications. It supports sending image data in RGB, RGBA, or PNG format, displaying and deleting images by identifier, position, or z-index, and managing layered graphics with cursor-relative placement. The positioning submodule handles layout calculations using integer coordinates to align images within terminal cells, while the identifier submodule generates and validates integer-based IDs for safe image referencing. Example uses include inline image rendering, dynamic image layering, and precise terminal screen layout control.
